# we were talking about the bias

Right — ICT Bias lifecycle is a different beast compared to RSI. Here's the key difference:

## ICT Bias vs RSI Lifecycle

|  | RSI Divergence | ICT Bias |
| :-- | :-- | :-- |
| Nature | One-time event signal | Continuous state signal |
| Storage | New row each detection | Upsert — always 1 row per symbol+timeframe |
| Closes when | Not detected + 15 candles | Bias **flips or goes RANGING** |
| Deleted when | 24h after closed | Never — just updates in place |

## The Problem Right Now

ICT Bias has **no close trigger at all**. It upserts every scan with the latest bias — but if a coin goes RANGING or gets delisted, the old BULLISH/BEARISH bias just sits there forever, never updated.

## What Needs to Happen

In `ict-bias.scanner.ts`, the `scan()` method already returns `0` when bias is RANGING:

```typescript
if (!sig || sig.bias === 'RANGING') return 0;
```

But it should also **close the existing signal** when that happens:

```typescript
if (!sig || sig.bias === 'RANGING') {
    await this.signalsService.closeIctBiasSignal(symbol, timeframe);
    return 0;
}
```

